race.comment: EXPRESS CODE (6) is fast and was an easy winner here on debut before coming back and folding up in a race a few grades higher than this. Fitter again and can get back on track. KING OF GERALDINE (9) rates well off the narrow first-up defeat at the Sunshine Coast in much stronger. He will be better for that but has to skip over from a wide barrier today and the 1.5kg apprentice will need a touch of luck. BOLD BIDDER (3) improved narrowly beaten a Warwick. That was his best show of form since the switch from the Baker yard in Sydney. He has plenty up his sleeve but the question is whether he can recapture it. SPIRITOF THE OCEAN (11) may be the next best building on the Kilcoy maiden win.
